Reasoning: The paper presents an algorithm for solving linear systems in 3-dimensional truss stiffness matrices, which arise from linear elasticity problems. The algorithm combines nested dissection and support theory to decompose the truss into separate and balanced regions with small boundaries, and then utilizes bounds on the spectrum of each region to obtain improved algorithms by preconditioning with partial states of separator-based Gaussian elimination. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE), and Multimedia (cs.MM).
